  "prompt": "What countries participate in The Commonwealth Games?",
  "response": "The Commonwealth Games, held every four years, feature countries that are members of the Commonwealth of Nations. As of 2023, there are 56 member countries that participate in the games. Some notable participants include:\n\n1. Australia\n2. Canada\n3. England\n4. India\n5. New Zealand\n6. Scotland\n7. South Africa\n8. Wales\n9. Jamaica\n10. Nigeria\n\nThe full list includes a diverse range of nations from different continents, including Africa, Asia, the Americas, and the Pacific. Each Games may also include teams from territories or regions that are associated with member countries. \n\nFor the most current and specific list of participating countries for a particular Commonwealth Games, it's best to refer to the official Commonwealth Games Federation website or the relevant organizing committee for that year's Games.",
